  "texts": [
    "This inclusion helps to avoid premature convergence on suboptimal solutions and improves the robustness and reliability of the WCET estimates.",
    "By encouraging a broader exploration of the solution space, our method enhances the overall performance and effectiveness of the algorithms.The contributions of this thesis aim to provide incremental improvements to the state-of-the-art in WCET analysis, with the hope of contributing to the development of more reliable and efficient real-time systems in increasingly complex and dynamic environments.",
    "Thesis OrganizationIn Chapter 2 provides the theoretical background essential for understanding the subsequent application of GAs and RL to WCET analysis.",
    "It covers key principles of real-time systems, GAs, RL, and WCET analysis techniques, establishing a conceptual method for the research.",
    "In Chapter 3, a detailed review of existing WCET techniques is presented, highlighting the evolution of these techniques in response to the changing landscape of computing architectures."
  ]
